1. Based on your chosen potential replace "???" in 'init.mod' and potential.mod. Keep these files in such a location so that they can access the potential files.

2. To run use <lammps executable file> in.elastic 

3. The log file will contain the information of the elastic constants at the end of the file. 

4. Read the preambles of "in.elastic" and "init.mod" files. Vary the value of "up" variable in init.mod upto +/- one roder and check if the results are the same. 

 
